## Git Workflow

- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `chore:`
- Never commit `.env` — use `.env.example` as the template
- Run lint and tests before pushing: `{{#if (eq packageManager "npm")}}npm run lint && npm test{{/if}}{{#if (eq packageManager "pnpm")}}pnpm lint && pnpm test{{/if}}{{#if (eq packageManager "yarn")}}yarn lint && yarn test{{/if}}{{#if (eq packageManager "bun")}}bun run lint && bun test{{/if}}`

## What NOT to Do

- Do not add speculative features — build what's needed now
- Do not use `any` — use `unknown` and narrow properly
- Do not bypass TypeScript errors with `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error` without explanation
- Do not add dependencies without checking if a built-in or existing dep can handle it
- Do not write functions longer than 50 lines without decomposing
- Do not commit secrets or `.env` files
